Name: Stim Packs
Description: Reduces the cooldown and increases the movement speed by 50%. Stim Pack effects are not cumulative. If the affected unit has 10 or less health they cannot use Stimpack.

Name: Lockdown
Description: Disables targeted mechanical unit.

Name: EMP Shockwave
Description: EMP fires a special missile that flies to the targeted point and explodes. Any unit or building within a 3-matrix radius of the blast point will have its shields and energy reduced to zero.

Name: Spider Mines
Description: Deploys a Spider Mine on the targeted spot. Spider Mines explode dealing 125 explosive damage.

Name: Scanner Sweep
Description: Temporarily reveals and provides detection for a targeted area on the map. Note that invisible enemies that move outside the range of the sweep remain visible until the scan wears off.

Name: Tank Siege Mode
Description: Transforms the Tank into Siege Mode where it gains Splash Damage, greatly increased range and damage at the cost of losing all mobility, having a minimum range, and a slower firing rate.

Name: Defensive Matrix
Description: Defensive Matrix creates a 250 Hit Point non-regenerating shield around the target unit. The effect wears off even if the shields haven't run out of Hit Points. Defensive Matrix has 0 armor and absorbs full damage of every damage type like protoss shields.

Name: Irradiate
Description: Irradiate surrounds the targeted unit with an aura of radioactive energy. It can be cast on any unit and deals 250 damage over a period of 37 in-game seconds to all biological units within a 2 hex radius of the affected unit.

Name: Yamato Gun
Description: Yamato Gun fires an intense blast of concentrated energy at the target, doing 260 points of explosive damage. The attack has a longer range than the Battlecruiser's sight range, allowing you to destroy towers and other defensive structures from a safe distance.

Name: Cloaking Field
Description: Makes the Wraith invisible to all units except when Detection is present.
Duration: Until it uncloaks or energy is depleted

Name: Personnel Cloaking
Description: Makes the Ghost invisible to all units except detectors.
Duration: Until it uncloaks or energy is depleted

Name: Restoration
Description: Removes Lockdown, Optic Flare, Irradiate, Plague, Ensnare, Parasite, and Maelstrom from targeted unit.

Name: Optical Flare
Description: This spell can be cast on a single unit. The sight range of the targeted unit is permanently reduced to 1 matrix. It also removes any detection ability that unit may possess. The affected unit will display a 'Blinded' tag in its information box when selected.

Name: Healing
Description: Automatically (or on order) heals a close-by friendly biological ground unit. On Fastest Game Speed, heals 18.6 health per second.

Name: Nuclear Strike
Description: Launches a nuclear strike at the targeted spot. Requires a Nuclear Silo equipped with a Nuke.

Name: Burrowing
Description: Burrow is a first tier Zerg ability that enables ground units to burrow in the ground, visible only to detectors. A burrowed unit cannot move or attack, but it still provides vision.

Name: Infestation
Description: Infests heavily damaged (< 1/2 HP) Terran Command Center to make an Infested Command Center.

Name: Spawn Broodlings
Description: A Queen with this ability can instantaneously destroy any non-robotic ground unit in the game as the Broodling larvae she plants rapidly mature and, feeding on the victim from the inside, destroy their host.

Name: Dark Swarm
Description: Dark Swarm is a defensive spell encompassing a 6x6 matrix area in which ground units take no damage from ranged weapons. Only melee attacks, splash damage, or special weaponry are able to affect a unit underneath Dark Swarm. The Dark Swarm lasts for approximately 38 seconds each time it is cast. All ground units, including enemy units, are protected.

Name: Plague
Description: Plague affects any unit or building with a 4x4 matrix of the target. A unit affected by a Plague slowly begins to lose hit points (at about 11.8 damage per second) until either the maximum of 300 points of damage is done or the unit reaches one health.

Name: Consume
Description: Consume replenishes the Defiler's energy points by sacrificing the life of one of your own Zerg units.

Name: Ensnare
Description: The viscous green goo expelled when a Queen uses her Ensnare ability will cover any unburrowed unit in a 4x4 matrix area, affecting them for about 25 seconds. Units covered with the goo have their movement rate cut by half. This can cause a host of problems for the enemy.

Name: Parasite
Description: Queens can launch the parasitic creatures onto the unsuspecting host from up to 12 matrices away. Once the Parasite is attached, the controller of the Parasite can now see what the affected unit sees. If a unit with cloak detection has an attached parasite, then cloaked units will also be seen by the Parasite.

Name: Lurker Aspect
Description: Enables Hydralisks to morph into Lurkers.

Name: Psionic Storm
Description: When casting Psionic Storm lightning-like images appear over a 3x3 matrix area. Units in this area rapidly receive 8 volleys of 14 damage. This damage is received regardless of armour or unit size. You can dodge Storms with proper micro, sparing your units from some damage.

Name: Hallucination
Description: Hallucination creates two Hallucinations which have the same appearance as a targeted unit - friendly or otherwise. To your enemy, these Hallucinations will look like regular units, whereas to you they will look like blueish copies, distinguishing them from your regular units.

Name: Recall
Description: Recall opens a 5x5 wormhole which teleports all friendly units in the wormhole to the caster. You cannot Recall allied units, only your own.

Name: Stasis Field
Description: Stasis Field freezes units in a 3x3 around the target area for approximately 60 in-game seconds. Stasised units cannot move, attack, be attacked or be affected by spells for the duration of the stasis.

Name: Archon Warp
Description: Two High Templars, when selected together, can merge into an Archon.

Name: Disruption Web
Description: Disruption Web affects a 120x80 pixel area for a short duration, preventing all units and buildings under it from attacking. Casters are still able to cast, and spider mines will still activate.

Name: Mind Control
Description: Mind Control is an offensive spell cast by the Protoss Dark Archon which dominates the mind of a single controllable unit, transferring control of the unit to the player who casts the spell. A unit Mind Controlled retains its unique upgrades, but not its bonuses to Attack, Armor or Shields.

Name: Dark Archon Meld
Description: Two Dark Templars, when selected together, can merge into a Dark Archon

Name: Feedback
Description: Feedback, when cast on unit, that unit loses all of its energy and will take the amount of damage equal to the energy lost.

Name: Maelstrom
Description: Maelstrom is an area of effect (3 matrix radius) ability that will instantly stun (prevents the affected units from moving, attacking, or utilizing any special abilities) all organic ground or air units for a short duration.
